OL,3,CHottest parts of UK revealed as
OL,4,Ctemperatures set to soar this week
OL,6,FWe are likely to see our warmest day
OL,7,Fof the year so far on both Tuesday and
OL,8,Fthen again on Wednesday, beating the
OL,9,Fcurrent high of 20.9C set last month.
OL,11,FEven 24C is still some way off the all
OL,12,Ftime April record of 29.4C from 16
OL,13,FApril 1949, but it does threaten the
OL,14,Fday record of 23.9C set a few years
OL,15,Fago on 8th April in 2020.
OL,17,FHow long will it last?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
